  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user i want to:\r\n- Be able to quickly scroll to bottom if i scrolled up a lot\r\n- See if there has been new messages since i scrolled up\r\n\r\nUser story for a `scroll to bottom message` with a unread messages counter badge:\r\n1. user opens a chat with no new messages\r\n2. scrolls to top, a `scroll to bottom` button appears (with no badge)\r\n3. a new incoming message received. used does not see it -> thereâ€™s `(1)` badge on the `scroll to bottom` button now\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: \r\n- Add a scroll to bottom button when user scrolled mare than 50% of screen height up. \r\n- Attach an unread messages counter ONLY if there has been new messages while user was looking on a scrolled screen\r\n\r\n![scroll to bottom](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3115606/41159293-b4f1555c-6b34-11e8-9284-4cdd32268131.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nZeplin:\r\nzpl.io/a74lOev\r\nzpl://screen?sid=5b1a7d3dce9f5b38704a1196&pid=5a55d587ba304eed4d2c942f",
